  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0ba3\u0bb5\u0bc0\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 54.6 \u0b9a\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b89\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Inflation rose sharply to 54.6 percent in June",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Inflation as measured by the Colombo Consumer Price Index rose significantly to 54.6 percent last June.",
        "Inflation rose to 15.5 percent in June from 39.1 percent in the previous month.",
        "The Central Bank of Sri Lanka (CBSL) has attributed the rise in inflation to the rise in prices of vegetables, fish, bread, rice and other non-food items such as transport, water, electricity, gas, services and tariffs over the past one month.",
        "As the country is facing a massive economic crisis, inflation is increasing rapidly due to the devaluation of the Sri Lankan rupee. In such a situation, according to the assessment carried out by the Colombo Consumer Price Index, inflation recorded a sharp increase in June compared to the previous month. The central bank said that the inflation was mostly driven by supply-side (supply of goods and services) factors.",
        "Pointing out that the monthly increase in the prices of food and non-food items is the main reason for the rise in inflation, the central bank said that food inflation, which was recorded as 57.4 percent last month, has increased to 80.1 percent in June, and non-food inflation, which was 30.6 percent in May, has increased to 42.4 percent in June.",
        "A report issued by the Central Bank stated that a significant increase was observed in the prices of food items including shellfish, vegetables, rice, palm, and other food items last month, and in terms of non-food items, the prices and charges of transport, restaurants, hotels, special classes for education, housing, water, electricity and gas increased.",
        "Meanwhile, the monthly change in the Colombo Consumer Price Index was recorded at 12.80 percent last June due to the increase in the prices of food and non-food items by 6.81 percent and 5.99 percent respectively.",
        "According to the estimate, central inflation, which reflects the basic inflation of the economy, rose to 39.9 percent in June from 28.4 percent last month. Meanwhile, average inflation rose to 13.3 per cent in June from 10.2 per cent in the previous month.",
        "Against this backdrop, the Colombo Consumer Price Index (WPI) inflation for the last six months of January, February, March, April, May and June was 14.2, 15.1, 18.7, 29.8, 39.1 and 54.6 percent respectively.",
        "Based on this, it is noteworthy that inflation, which showed a moderate increase in the first quarter of this year, has shown a sharp increase in the second quarter - especially a 10 percent monthly increase."
      ],
